1- Run npx create-expo-module --local to create a new module within your project. This will generate a modules folder containing the necessary native code structure for your module.

2-Inside the generated module's ios and android directories, you'll find example files (e.g., ExpoMyModuleModule.swift for iOS, ExpoMyModuleModule.kt for Android).
Modify these files to implement your desired native functionality. This includes defining functions or views that you want to expose to JavaScript.

3- Import custom native module

        import ExpoMyModule from 'expo-my-module'; // Replace 'expo-my-module' with your module name


4- Build from main project
        import ExpoMyModule from 'expo-my-module'; // Replace 'expo-my-module' with your module name
